metadata.name: Siena #95
metadata.description:
Siena is a generative piece creating trails made with Javascript.
This piece is based on researches of an upcoming piece called RIO.
Algorithm written in Siena, Italia by Quentin Hocdé - 15/11/2021.
Each token have a unique color theme, and each square's size and positions are generated.

metadata.name: d/e/m/boss TWO #66
metadata.description:
TWO combines a couple of distribution algorithms, one that creates a mesh with different variations and the other that plays with packing probabilities.

Please be patient, it takes a while to render (30-60 secs) and draws around 6M circles during 4 steps.

Responsive, zoom out browser window and refresh to get a larger output.
's' save the current canvas

TWO is part of a series playing with textures creating emboss/deboss effect.

/boss

metadata.name: CHX-1 #109
metadata.description:
Glitching pixels like it’s 1999.

Inspired by 90’s digital aesthetics, CHX-1 takes a random selection of GAN seeds, combines them in unique ways, and processes them –individually and as a group– with a series of glitching dithering algorithms. Generating fun, original, colorful artworks. Millions of possibilities. Have fun!

<<< Base seeds generated offline using personal styleGAN2-ADA models. Image processing and combinations done generatively by the CHX-1 algorithm >>>

GAN –> p5js –> Blockchain


• Artworks can take a few seconds to load when running live code.

• Press “s” (when "open live" is active) to save a PNG image.

metadata.name: reKäp #10
metadata.description:
Chaotic bursts of vertexes, 2022 edition.
Reminiscent of early 2000s flyer design && Macromedia Freehand abuse
hbd (fx)hash! 

Artwork renders in 4:5 aspect by default, 
press space to render artwork in window size.
Press 2/3 to render in double/triple resolution
Press s to save canvas


100% of primary to Tezos4Iran
